I think what Cook is saying is that if a site is to retain credibility and accuracy, then censorship -  ie removal of posts should be discouraged.<br><br>
The point of contention - posts which describe Vietnam Veterans as murderers and baby killers - contribute to historic accuracy.<br><br>
There are historic revisionists who would have us believe that The Holocaust never happened. The same can be applied concerning taunting Veterans who returned from Vietnam.<br><br>
Marc can do whatever he pleases, of course.
